          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Each neutron detector consisted of a 25mm",
                "thick NE104 plastic scintillator of diameter 125mm",
                "viewed by two Phillips XP1040 photomultiplier tubes."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The samples consisted of right circular annuli of the",
                "material \"Teflon\" (CnFn) with (outer) diameter 63.5",
                "mm, wall thickness 22.7 mm and height 100 mm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron energy spectra were measured at",
                "bremsstrahlung end-point energies varying between 16",
                "and 25 MeV, in 1 MeV steps. At each end-point energy,",
                "eight neutron-energy spectra were measured",
                "simultaneously for angles between 48 degrees and 139",
                "degrees, in 13 degree steps, using neutron",
                "time-of-flight techniques over 10 m flight paths."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "4PI1A"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The cross-section scale of the total angle-",
                "integrated cross section was determined from measured",
                "deuterium data (D20 minus H20; measured sequentially",
                "in cycles with the 19F) by use of calculations by",
                "Arenhovel et al. and Partovi)."
              ]
            }
          ],
